          "vnum": 2139,
          "name": "Western Channel",
          "description": "This wide channel allows ships to pass between the cliff to the south and the low-lying reef you can see to the north. In the distance to the east you can discern the mouth of a small bay. A dark opening gapes at you from the cliff face.",
